definition.value: A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-gallocatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a (4alpha->6)-linkage.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (-)-epicatechin and (+)-gallocatechin units joined by a (4beta->8)-linkage.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (-)-epigallocatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a (4alpha->6)-linkage.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-catechin and (+)-gallocatechin units joined by a (4alpha->6)-linkage.
An anthocyanin cation that is delphinidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(cis-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue
An anthocyanin cation that is delphinidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue
An anthocyanin cation that is delphinidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An oligonucleotide comprised of 21 thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
An oligonucleotide comprised of six thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
A triglyceride in which the 1- and 3-acyl groups are palmitoyl while that at position 2 is oleoyl.
An anthocyanin cation that is malvidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
A polyether antibiotic which affects ion transport and ATPase activity in mitochondria. It is produced by Streptomyces hygroscopicus.
An epoxy(hydroxy)icosatrienoic acid consisting of (5Z,9E,14Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid having additional (8R)-hydroxy- and (11R,12R)-epoxy groups.
An anthocyanin cation that is malvidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(cis-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An epoxy(hydroxy)icosatrienoic acid consisting of (5Z,9E,14Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid having additional (8R)-hydroxy- and (11S,12S)-epoxy groups.
An anthocyanin cation that is malvidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue
An oligonucleotide comprised of 21 2'-deoxycytidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
An epoxy(hydroxy)icosatrienoic acid consisting of (5Z,8Z,14Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid having additional (10R)-hydroxy- and (11S,12S)-epoxy groups.
An anthocyanin cation that is peonidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An oligonucleotide comprised of fifteen 2'-deoxyguanosine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
An oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of eight adenosine, five thymidine and a further eight adenosine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
A glycosylglucose consisting of D-glucose with undefined anomeric stereochemistry and an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at the 3-position.
An epoxy(hydroxy)icosatrienoic acid consisting of (5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid having additional (13R)-hydroxy- and (14S,15S)-epoxy groups.

A racemate composed of equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-sarin. A potent and irreversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase that is toxic to the nervous system and is employed as a chemical warfare agent.
An oligonucleotide comprised of five 2-deoxyuridine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
The (R)-enantiomer of 2-(4-chloro-2-methylphenoxy)propanoic acid; the active stereoisomer of the racemic herbicide mecoprop.
A monocarboxylic acid that is lactic acid in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a 4-chloro-2-methylphenyl group.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group from D-glucosaminate 6-phosphate.
An anthocyanin cation that is peonidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(cis-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An anthocyanin cation that is peonidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue
An anthocyanin cation that is petunidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(cis-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An anthocyanin cation that is petunidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue
An oligonucleotide comprised of two thymidine residues connected via a 3'->5' phosphodiester linkage.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-mecoprop.
The (S)-enantiomer of 2-(4-chloro-2-methylphenoxy)propanoic acid; the inactive stereoisomer of the racemic herbicide mecoprop.
An oligonucleotide comprised of twelve thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
The canonical deoxyribonucleotide residue formed from dUMP (2'-deoxy-5'-uridylic acid).
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a uridylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a uridylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3R,4R)-3,4-dihydroxycyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carboxylic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A monomethoxyflavone that is apigenin in which the hydroxy group at position 7 is methylated.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of cuevaene A, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is an O-glucuronidated derivative of kaempferol.
A kaempferol O-glucuronide that is kaempferol with a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue attached at the 3-position.
A tertiary alcohol that is cyclohexanol substituted at positions 1 and 2 by 3-methoxyphenyl and dimethylaminomethyl groups respectively.
A kaempferol O-glucuronide that is kaempferol with a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue attached at the 5-position.
A kaempferol O-glucuronide that is kaempferol with a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue attached at the 7-position.

A 2-[(dimethylamino)methyl]-1-(3-methoxyphenyl)cyclohexanol in which both stereocentres have R-configuration; the (R,R)-enantiomer of the racemic opioid analgesic tramadol, it exhibits ten-fold higher analgesic potency than the (S,S)-enantiomer.
